<h1>Aspell package for R</h1>
<p align="right"><a href="@SRC_TAR@">Source  (@VERSION@)</a></p>

This R package provides an interface to the aspell library for
checking the spelling of words and documents.  The library is part of
the GNU software and provides a flexible framework for spelling with
customized dictionaries, filters, and so on.

<br>
Documentation on aspell can be found at
<a
href="http://aspell.sourceforge.net">http://aspell.sourceforge.net</a>.
The source code, binaries and dictionaries for aspell are also available from there.

<P>

This package provides access to these library facilities from within
R.  One can check the spelling of words, obtain suggetsions for
corrections, check an entire document sequentially customize the
speller, maintain different spellers for different purposes, and add
new words and provide corrections for the speller to use in the
future.

<h2>The Code</h2>

To use this package, one needs to have the aspell library installed.
Also, one needs to have one or more suitable dictionaries.


The R package is available as source as
<a href="@SRC_TAR@">Aspell</a>.
This can be installed as

<pre>
 R CMD INSTALL Aspell_0.1-0.tar.gz
</pre>

or directly from within R as
<pre>
install.packages("Aspell", repos = "http://www.omegahat.org/R")
</pre>


<h2>Dictionaries</h2>
Before you can actually use the <i class="rfunc">>aspell</i> function,
